jobs_results.description:
We are looking for a Business Analyst to be part of the Risk Management team, to enhance and support systems related to Credit Risk activities within the bank.

Mandatory Skill(s)
• Degree in Banking / Information Technology or other related fields;
• At least 2 to 8 years of Business Analyst experience in financial institutions;
• Possess good understanding of the life cycle of credit risk applications;
• Strong knowledge in database management, good hands-on in using SQL query;
• Hands on experience with Agile and project management;
• Analytical, detail-oriented and solution-oriented;
• Resourceful, independent and proactive team player;
• Good communication skills, good grasp of the current state and evolution of financial markets.

Desirable Skill(s)
• FRM Certified.
• Exposure on credit risk domain.

Responsibilities
• Gather, collate and analyse user requirements and provide clear business documents;
• Conduct business requirement walk-through with users and key stakeholders;
•... Perform data profiling and identify requirement gaps while performing UAT;
• Creating and executing test cases and coordinating User Acceptance Test (UAT);
• Perform UAT, report and track all testing issues and perform root cause analysis;
• Provide support to queries from business users and manage production issues;
• Ensure necessary changes/enhancements are implemented and documented
